                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3280: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-21T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 21, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 21—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1113. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 21, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Headquarters reports that the first railway battalion was sent
                                this morning from Ssupingkai to clear out 7,000 bandits in the
                                Changtu, Faku region.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>An official reception in celebration of the formation of the
                                Provincial Government was held yesterday.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
